text.tspan: Allow managing the results sections directly: add new search providers, hide unwanted sections
Show the file and folder results in sections, for easier navigation
Custom layouts for some results types, so they look better and the view isn't too repetitive
Secondary action for documents opens the file location.
Special-case some types of search results (calculations, file and folder search, software results): give them custom layouts, extra information
Allow expanding each section of results in place, to allow deeper navigation from shell search itself
Bigger thumbnails (but don't scale up smaller ones!)

Search results always have a primary action, which typically opens the search result. They can also optionally have a secondary action, which is triggered with Ctrl+Return, or with an icon button on the row.
Filesystem results are divided into 6 sections: documents, audio, videos, images, folders, files.
Make it easier to see, hear, type , point and click
Each section shows a maximum of 5 results.
If there are more than 5 results, a "Show All" button is shown in the section header.
When the header has keyboard focus, the return key activates the show all button (indicated by changing the label color).
Activating show all: the section header scrolls up to the top, all results in that section are shown, and the other sections are dimmed out.
Keyboard focus remains in the header. "Show All" changes to "Hide All".
This transition is potentially not great for pointer interaction, but works well with a keyboard.
